snippet.textDisplay: Its really embarrassing, I experienced the failure first hand. On Sunday March 1 I had a presentation from an old Italian wimemaker who had a sneezing fit and I got sick the next day. I'm a server and as it always goes when sick my boss told me if I need to miss a second day with a fever I must have a doctors note, no sick days or pto of course. My dr. Office said I cant come in with flu like symptoms or have a Dr. Note without being seen by a Dr., Catch .22. They want me to do a FaceTime with a doc for 80 bucks and miss a day of work, that's like a 200 to 250 dollar swing which I cant do and expect to make rent and bills. Btw that's stupid too that my Dr. Cant take my word but magically they will when i pay a bill and they can see my face, wtf cant take my word on the phone though. I basically begged for the test to be done because my symptoms matched, I'm asthmatic but in good shape and relatively young and had noticed the abnormal fatigue, shortness of breath was uncanny in that it's never happened to me like that with the flu where youre fine but then get the panic for air feeling out of nowhere, which became walking pneumonia in my opinion with my cough and it was a little hard on me, but of course my main concern was infecting my parents or others and not me as I'm hearty. I was basically told I wont be tested until I'm on my death bed because I'm young and healthy. I'll never know if I had it, could have been the flu, but I stayed away from my parents who are in their 60s and 70s and anybody I cared about, but I still went to work serving food. After 2 weeks my lungs got better. The financial insecurity I now have is embarrassing in America, the recklessness not to test everyone and especially those with symptoms is unconscionable, rich people and basketball teams are getting tested without symptoms, the classism is laid bare.
